Usage: add_cell_obs [-help] -cell <cell_name_or_pointer> [-exceptPGNet]
                    -layer <layer_name_or_pointer> [-mask <integer>] [-spacing <float> | -design_rule_width <float>] {-rects {{llx1 lly1 urx1 ury1} {llx2 lly2 urx2 ury2}...}> | -polygon { <x1 y1> <x2 y2> <x3 y3> ...}}

-help                            # Prints out the command usage
-cell <cell_name_or_pointer>     # Cell name or pointer, ilm cell also can be
                                 # supported.
                                 # ((libCell/ptnCell|topCell|vCell), required)
-design_rule_width <float>       # Specify design rule width (float, optional)
-exceptPGNet                     # Indicates that Power/Ground routing is
                                 # ignored when checking for DRC violations
                                 # (including shorts) involving the added obs.
                                 # It's equivalent to LEF MACRO OBS LAYER
                                 # EXCEPTPGNET. (bool, optional)
-layer <layer_name_or_pointer>   # Layer name or pointer ((layer), required)
-mask <integer>                  # Specify mask. (uint, optional)
-polygon { <x1 y1> <x2 y2> <x3 y3> ...}    # Obs polygon.
                                           # (point_list, optional)
-rects {{llx1 lly1 urx1 ury1} {llx2 lly2 urx2 ury2}...}>
                                 # obs rect lists (box_list, optional)
-spacing <float>                 # Specify spacing value (float, optional)